content: an accelerator. The tamper-resistant hardware security module, which is contained on the Crypto Express6S feature, conforms to the Federal Information Processing Standard (FIPS) 140-2 Level 4 Certification. It supports User Defined Extension (UDX) services to implement cryptographic functions and algorithms (when defined as an IBM CCA coprocessor). The following CCA compliance levels are available:  Non-compliant (default)  PCI-HSM 2016  PCI-HSM 2016 (migration, key tokens while migrating to compliant) The following EP11 compliance levels are available (Crypto Express6S and Crypto Express5S):  FIPS 2009 (default)  FIPS 2011  BSI 2009  BSI 2011 Each Crypto Express6S feature occupies one I/O slot in the PCIe I/O drawer, and features no CHPID assigned. However, it includes one PCHID. 4.8 Integrated Firmware Processor The Integrated Firmware Processor (IFP) was introduced with the zEC12 and zBC12. The IFP is used to support firmaware partitions and for managing PCIe native
